body: Thanks for reporting, I'll take a look today
Thanks! Let me know if I can help :)

Maybe something is wrong with the dependency? I can't reproduce the problem... Try to delete the folder and run again:

```
$ rm -rf ~/.m2/repository/com/jcabi
```

Still the same. I also tried to delete my repo (some days ago), but to no
avail...
Strange error message... This also happens with 0.7.19.

Maybe that's just a false alarm and the problem comes from somewhere else.
(Did you try with Maven 3.1?).

Hmm..

Anyway - thanks for your efforts!

Raphael

It's too early to say "thank you", let's fix the problem first :) Yes, I tested with Maven 3.1.1. But I didn't do a full integration test. Let me try to create it...
I added an integration test in f25368e and it doesn't reproduce the problem, neither with Maven 3.0.3 nor with 3.1.1...
I don't think that this is because of `jcabi-aether.jar`.. Did you try to remove it from `pom.xml` and build again? I mean, are you sure that this particular dependency causes the problem?

Hey Yegor,

I added a "showcase". Have a look at : https://github.com/ninjaframework/ninja/tree/feature-maven-plugin/ninja-maven-plugin. If I build it I get the strange error message. If I remove jcabi-aether the problem goes away.

This does NOT mean that jcabi is the culprit. It may well be something else - computers are strange :)

Thanks for your support. I hope I can use jcabi-aether - it sound like exactly what I need!

Best,

Raphael
Hm... I downloaded your pom.xml and successfully executed it with Maven 3.0.3. Maybe something is wrong with your maven?

Hmm. You built ninja-maven-plugin (and not the parent ninja) - right? Well. I am using Maven 3.1. But apart from that that's more than strange. Maybe because I am on a Mac... I am dealing with a lot of Maven projects and builds on a daily basis - and I don't have any problems with them. Sorry about that... And thanks for your support... I'll try to implement it with raw aether then I guess...
I'm also on Mac, but with Maven 3.0.3. I tried only the `pom.xml`, not the entire project. Let me try to clone everything and build the entire plugin.
